race.comment: GLAD YOU THINK SO (5) hunted out from the wide gate when sitting on the pace for a gritty second over 2000m at Randwick in BM78 grade. Back to his best and worth noting he's got a solid win record at this course. Senior rider on and will stalk the speed. Hard to hold out. BELLE DETELLE (10) progressive mare who returned for her four-year-old season with a closing third from last on the turn, over 1500m at Randwick. Has the class to win this. INQUIRING MINDS (7) relished the jump in trip and heavy track when a determined winner in the small field over 1800m at Rosehill. Finds a tougher race and sure to be thereabouts despite drawing out. KIND WORDS (11) talented mare unlucky not to have a few more wins on her CV. Engaged in a thrilling on speed battle in the heavy conditions when a narrow second over 1800m at Rosehill. Only needs an ounce of luck to figure prominently. BARAZIN (9) total forgive when fourteenth from the wide draw in the Little Dance. Value contender.
